"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The DBSCAN implementation in scikit-learn requires the input data to be either a feature array or a distance matrix if the metric is set to 'precomputed'. In the provided code, the custom distance function 'get_point_distance' is used directly as the metric, which is not supported by DBSCAN. The metric parameter should be a string or a callable that is one of the options allowed by sklearn.metrics.pairwise_distances.\",\n  \"patch\": \"35c35,36\\n< clustering = DBSCAN(metric=get_point_distance).fit(\\n---\\n> from sklearn.metrics import pairwise_distances\\n> clustering = DBSCAN(metric='precomputed').fit(pairwise_distances(np.array([point.to_list() for point in points]), metric=get_point_distance))\\n\"\n}"